Introduction

Yeseo is a South Korean singer, dancer, and actress under 143 Entertainment. She is a member of the girl group MADEIN.

She was a member of the kids group CutieL, with whom she debuted with on December 17, 2010.

Yeseo joined Busters on February 1, 2019, following Minjung's departure in January. A year later, on July 31, 2020, it was reported that Yeseo eventually left Busters.

In July 2021, Yeseo was revealed to be a participant in the Mnet girl group survival show "Girls Planet 999." She ended up placing sixth on the final episode, securing her spot as a member of the girl group Kep1er. She debuted as a member of Kep1er on January 3, 2022, with their first mini-album "First Impact" and the title track "WA DA DA."

It was announced in June 2024 that Yeseo would leave Kep1er as her contract expired and would join 143 Entertainment's girl group MADEIN.
